Her Wikipedia entry (with exactly as much drama as the photo might suggest--she packed a lot into just 33 years of living):
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adah_Isaacs_Menken" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adah_Isaacs_Menken</a>
She wrote, near the end of her life:  &quot;I am lost to art and life. Yet, when all is said and done, have I not at my age tasted more of life than most women who live to be a hundred? It is fair, then, that I should go where old people go.&quot;
